The paper discusses the development of Web service networks for automatic discovery and composition, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The use of similarity metrics such as Levenshtein, Jaro, and Jaro-Winkler suggests a focus on Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Information Retrieval (IR), which are subcategories of cs.DL and cs.IR respectively. Finally, the study of topological properties of networks and the ongoing research on syntactic Web services suggest a connection to Software Engineering (cs.SE).
